## Priority Guidelines

<!-- STATIC -->
### Critical Priority
- Core functionality broken
- Authentication/security issues
- Data loss or corruption
- Application crashes
- **Action:** Drop everything and resolve immediately

<!-- STATIC -->
### High Priority
- Important features not working
- Significant user experience issues
- Performance problems
- **Action:** Resolve at next logical stopping point

<!-- STATIC -->
### Low Priority
- Minor functionality issues
- Edge cases
- Polish improvements
- **Action:** Add to planned work

